('manhattan-associates', 'Manhattan Associates', 'Unified supply chain commerce platform for WMS, TMS, and omnichannel retail fulfillment',
 E'Manhattan Associates is a leading provider of supply chain and omnichannel commerce software, best known for its warehouse management system (WMS) and active omni platform for unified retail commerce. The company serves major retailers, wholesale distributors, and manufacturers that need enterprise-grade warehouse and distribution technology built for the complexity of modern e-commerce fulfillment alongside traditional retail and wholesale operations.\n\nThe AI and machine learning capabilities in Manhattan''s platform focus on intelligent labor management, slot optimization, and demand-driven replenishment. The WMS uses AI to optimise warehouse slotting - which SKUs are placed in which locations - based on pick velocity, co-pick frequency, and weight considerations, reducing travel distance per order pick. Labor management uses historical performance data and real-time workload projections to set engineered standards and predict staffing needs across shifts. The Active Omni platform uses AI to optimise order routing decisions in real time - determining whether an order should be fulfilled from a DC, a store, or a third-party logistics partner based on current inventory position, shipping cost, and delivery speed.\n\nManhattan Associates serves Tapestry (Coach, Kate Spade), Williams-Sonoma, Carter''s, and hundreds of global retailers and distributors. The company''s SCALE architecture is fully cloud-native, allowing continuous updates and new AI capability deployment without the lengthy upgrade cycles that plagued on-premise WMS implementations. For retailers and distributors where warehouse and fulfillment operations are a core competitive differentiator, Manhattan Associates'' depth in execution-layer AI is among the strongest in the market.',
 'https://manh.com', 'https://manh.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.5, 2600, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['warehouse-management', 'supply-chain', 'logistics'],
 ARRAY['Industry-leading WMS with AI-powered slotting, labor management, and fulfillment optimization', 'Active Omni platform intelligently routes orders across DC, store, and 3PL in real time', 'Cloud-native SCALE architecture enables continuous AI updates without upgrade projects', 'Deep retail and omnichannel expertise - strong for complex e-commerce + store fulfillment'],
 ARRAY['Enterprise pricing and implementation scope - not suitable for SMB or mid-market operations', 'Implementation timelines of 12-24 months for full WMS deployment', 'Best value for companies with large, high-throughput distribution operations', 'Smaller logistics providers may find the platform over-engineered for simpler needs'],
 ARRAY['Large retailer warehouse management and AI-optimized fulfillment for omnichannel operations', 'Wholesale distributor WMS modernisation replacing legacy on-premise systems with cloud-native platform', 'E-commerce brand order routing optimization across DC, store, and 3PL fulfillment nodes'],
